The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 The working committee of Mohun Bagan passed the resolution to build Mohun Bagan Sports Research Foundation (MBSRF), a residential sports complex for the footballers, in a meeting on Friday.

 The club is looking for 60 acres of land in a nearby location for the purpose. ?Every year we are having problems regarding the availability of ground. After this foundation is over (approximately 10 years), we will use our present ground to play only the final matches and other important matches in any meets,? said club secretary Anjan Mitra.

 The club secretary is going to approach the state government for a suitable land.

 Calcutta Port Trust ousted Bengal President?s XI 1-0 in a Beighton Cup Hockey meet match at the CC amp;FC on Friday. Sunil Waribum Singh scored the all-important goal in the 28 th minute.

 Eastern Railway Sports Association (ERSA) booked a final berth after they defeated Burra Bazar Yubak Sabha 76-62 in the semi-finals of the Division I Knockout Basketball championships on Friday. ERSA will meet Calcutta Port Trust (CPT) in the final. 

